In a large bowl, mix the minced beef, egg and parsley together. Season to taste.Now take a teaspoon of mixture and, in your hand, roll it into a ball. Dust the ball in flour and put to one side. Repeat  with the rest of the mixture.In a frying pan, gently saut√© the onions and chilli in the olive oil until soft.Add the meatballs and gently fry until golden brown.Now add the red wine and simmer for approximately two minutes. Once the wine has evaporated, pour in the chopped tomatoes.  Season to taste and cook for a further four minutes.In the meantime, cook the pasta in boiling, salted water until al dente. Drain and add to the sauce.Mix well and serve with freshly grated pecorino.